name: Nike Dunk Low Pro SB "Mondrian"
description: The Piet Modrian Dunk Low has landed at KicksOnUs, and while the shoe does carry a fresh look in a simplistic way, one should consider the history of the inspiration. Piet Mondrian was a Dutch artist born in the latter part of the 19th century that developed the unique style of grid based paintings. What seems so simple carries its unique beauty with thick black lines forming rectangles filled only with primary colors or left white. In a time where virtually any pattern, color, or material can be applied to a sneaker, sometimes it is the most basic and simplistic styles that look right. Paying homage in the best way, these Dunk Lows are made of canvas tying back to Mondrian’s medium for this artwork. Add the Nike Dunk Low Pro SB "Mondrian" to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.

name: Nike Dunk Low Premium "Doernbecher"
description:
Words of inspiration etch the Nike Dunk Low “Doernbecher”. Designed in 2007 by Lance Dillon during chemotherapy treatment, this Doernbecher design sees help from Nike’s Mark Smith in the form of laser detailing. The model features a mix of black and green leather with lasered text appearing in all-over fashion. Now 24-years old with a degree in anthropology from Oregon State, Lance reflects favorably on his experience designing his “Doernbecher” Dunks. “Getting to work with the Nike staff and design my own shoe are things that I will always remember. But the greatest part of it was knowing that it was helping other kids that were going through the same things that I went through.” Although this same pair was released again this year, this exact pair is the original from 2006. Add the Nike Dunk Low Premium "Doernbecher" to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.
*NOTE*

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme "Doernbecher"
description: This is the Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme "Doernbecher" edition. In 2004, Nike created the Nike Doernbecher Freestyle initiative which would allow a child from the Doernbecher Children's Hospital to design a color way of a Nike shoe for which all proceeds from retail sales would go to the Doernbecher Foundation. This year six children were allowed to design their own shoe creating for the first time a variety of different Doernbecher models and increasing the funds raised. This Air Force 1 was designed by Chad Berg, a 15 year old who had a kayaking accident and nearly lost his life. He was in full cardiac arrest with no pulse and was transferred to the hospital after three hours of CPR. A machine which could function as his lungs and heart kept him alive while he recovered. Miraculously after 2 weeks, Chad was recovered without any neurological damage. Chad designed this Air Force 1 in the green of his favorite college team the Oregon Ducks. He chose to include carbon fiber panels and a glow in the dark outsole. The insole features his favorite saying, "The people who turn out the best are those people who make the best out of the way things turn out." Add the Nike Air Force 1 Low "Doernbecher" to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.

Add the Reebok Kamikaze II Mid "Glow In The Dark" to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.

name: Bodega x Reebok Classic Leather Lux "U.S.B.D.G.A."
description:
With their first Reebok collaboration in over two years, Bodega brings a military aesthetic to the “U.S.B.D.G.A.” Drawing from a history of military nicknames assigned to specialized military divisions a la The Screaming Eagles, the Bodega unit are the “Killer Bee Stingers”. A purveyor of hidden gems and hard-to-find goods, Bodega styles itself as a special military unit, with this Reebok collaboration being a part of the unit’s uniform. 

Featuring a desert camouflage mid-panel, the “U.S.B.D.G.A.” possesses two suede panels: a mustard suede perforated toe-box and a peanut butter suede heel cup. The heel tab is accented by a heel tab with tri-color stripes similar to stripes designated to enlisted members of the military. The Bodega logo, embossed on the tongue of the sneakers, compliments the pair with a subtle touch, while the name “Bodega Stingers” imprints the heels of the shoes to display the wearer’s allegiance. An off-white midsole and gum outsole accents the collaboration. Lastly, a Bodega patch stamps the left sole, featuring the division motto: Don’t Get Stung. Add the Bodega x Reebok Classic Leather Lux "U.S.B.D.G.A." to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.

name: Mita Sneakers x Reebok Classic Leather 30th Anniversary
description: It’s not often that chambray, loopback terry, pig suede and glow-in-the-dark stars come together on one pair of shoes, but Mita Sneakers somehow manages to make it work. The Mita x Reebok Classic Leather 30th Anniversary is the latest in a string of Reebok Classic Leather 30th Anniversary releases this year, and it’s arguably the most intriguing of the lot. A study in contrast and texture, the silhouette sports a mix-and-match combo of silky pig suede overlays, chambray underlays with glow-in-the-dark stars and suns, and soft, loopback terry collar linings. Adding more ingredients to the visual feast, meanwhile, is the use of a gum rubber outsole, along with Mita Sneakers-branded tongue woven labels, lace tips and sockliners. Add the Mita Sneakers x Reebok Classic Leather 30th Anniversary to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.

name: Frank The Butcher x Reebok Classic Leather "BAU"
description: Reebok teams up with another notable figure in the sneaker world for its latest Classic Leather release celebrating the coveted sneaker model’s 30 glorious years on the market. Collaborating with Frank The Butcher this time around, the sneaker is based off the Classic Leather R12 silhouette and boasts an upper made from premium navy leather and rich khaki suede. With an emphasis on making the shoe look “faster,” color blocking is used to give the sneaker the appearance of leaning forward — as seen in the navy heel portions of the cap and outsole. Frank leaves his mark in the form of a “Business as Usual” sock liner, a flow-molded hangtag, a custom “BAU” deubré for each side, and Frank The Butcher tabs at the tongue. Add the Frank The Butcher x Reebok Classic Leather "BAU" to your collection today from KicksOnUs.com.
